					<div class="aefis-formitem" data-aefis-formitem-id="8528" data-aefis-formitem-code="TEXT" data-aefis-history-id="25429" style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact">
									<div class="aefis-formItem-name-container row-fluid" style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;width: 100%;*zoom: 1;margin-bottom: 10px;font-size: 1.3em;font-weight: 400 !important">
										<h3 style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: inherit;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;padding: 0 !important;margin: 0 !important;font-size: 1.17em;line-height: 1.2em !important;font-family: &quot;DM Sans&quot;, sans-serif !important;font-weight: 400 !important;text-rendering: optimizelegibility;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact">Expanded Course Description:&nbsp;</h3>
									</div>
							<div class="aefis-formItem-options-container" style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;margin: 0px !important;font-size: 1.0em">
						<div class="aefis-formitem-options-container" style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;white-space: normal" data-aefis-enable-multiple-entires="false" data-aefis-empty-textarea="<div class=&quot;span11&quot;><textarea id=&quot;idhere&quot; name=&quot;idhere&quot; class=&quot;span11 editor&quot; data-aefis-formitem-option-id=&quot;8689&quot;></textarea></div>">
								<div class="form-item-option-text--response-container " style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact">
									<p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em"></p><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">This course covers the design of digital systems using VHSIC Hardware Description Language (VHDL) and its implementation in Field Programmable Gate Arrays (FPGAs). This technology allows cost-effective unique system realizations by enabling design reuse and simplifying custom circuit design. The design tools are first introduced and used to implement basic circuits. More advanced designs follow, focusing on integrating the FPGA with external peripherals, simple data processing applications, utilizing soft-core processors, and using intellectual property (IP) cores.</p><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">No specific course is required as a pre-requisite. However, a solid understanding of digital logic fundamentals is required.</p><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">
								</p></div>
						</div>
							</div>
					</div>
																</div>
															</div>
														</div>
