<p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">For research help, refer to the <a href="https://guides.library.jhu.edu/how-to" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #0077b3;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0);-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;font-weight: inherit">Research&nbsp;How-To&nbsp;Guides</a> or <a href="https://www.library.jhu.edu/library-services/research-consultation/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #0077b3;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0);-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;font-weight: inherit">schedule a research consultation</a>.&nbsp;</p>
Some, though not all, electronic versions of textbooks may be available through the Sheridan Libraries. <strong style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;font-weight: bold;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact">There is no guarantee that an electronic textbook is available.</strong> Please email <a href="mailto:asklib@jhu.edu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #0077b3;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0);-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;font-weight: inherit">asklib@jhu.edu</a> if you have any questions about searching for available eBooks.
