adjust: exact;border: 1px solid #777;padding: 5px"><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">10%</p></td></tr><tr style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;page-break-inside: avoid"><td style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;border: 1px solid #777;padding: 5px"><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">Exam</p></td><td style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;border: 1px solid #777;padding: 5px"><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">35%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">&nbsp;</p><h2 style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: inherit;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;padding: 0;font-family: &quot;DM Sans&quot;, sans-serif !important;font-weight: bold;font-size: 31.5px;line-height: 40px;margin: 10px 0;text-rendering: optimizelegibility;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact">Late Assignment Submissions Due to Travel</h2><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">It happens that students will have work-related travel plans and will be in a situation where they cannot work on a particular assignment due to lack of internet access or the lack of personal time due to extended work days or both. If you know you will have travel plans, please inform the instructor ahead of time. While difficult, it is possible to catch up with the course work and material due to missing one week of class. However, missing more than one week of class will make it very difficult to catch up and submit subsequent assignments on time. It is the students' responsibility to manage their travel plans during the semester and to catch up on all course material. <strong style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;font-weight: bold;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact">The policy remains that assignment submitted more than one week after the due date will not be accepted.</strong></p><p style="visibility: hidden;background-color: transparent;color: #333333;text-decoration: none;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;padding: 0;font-weight: 400;line-height: inherit;font-size: inherit;letter-spacing: 0;margin: 0 0 10px;padding-bottom: 0em;padding-top: 0em">
								</p></div>
						</div>
							</div>
					</div>
